RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 81. Maiden Special Weight Purse 61000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In The Last 3 Starts Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KOPION broke well then settled outside rivals, moved to within range four deep entering the turn, bid outside the top pair then dueled with SHE'S A TEMPEST three wide entering the stretch, put away inner rival approaching the eighth pole and drew off under hand urging. SHE'S A TEMPEST vied three deep early then dueled outside TOULOUSE DETRAC, cleared that rival past the five-sixteenths pole then had to battled with KOPION with a quarter mile left to run, fought two wide into the lane, could not match strides with the winner in upper stretch but was clearly second best. CRITICISM tracked off the rail up the backstretch then went between rivals nearing the turn, exited the bend three deep and churned on for a clear third. ULTIMATE AUTHORITY showed early speed between rivals then got put in a bit tight at the nine-sixteenths pole but did not lose much ground, chased the top pair three deep between rivals into the turn, got put in a bit tight again early on the bend, traveled four deep into the lane and weakened. DISCREPANCY broke a step slow, moved down to the inside to give chase, suffered a mild shuffle behind TOULOUSE DETRAC on the turn before gaining an opening along the rail, then weakened in the drive. TOULOUSE DETRAC vied inside a pair of rivals then dueled with SHE'S A TEMPEST, could not keep pace with outer rivals approaching the quarter pole and faded down the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: LAMBEAU sped clear and showed the way early while moving inside, met bids from outer pair on the turn, came off the rail a bit into the stretch allowing JAMMING EDDY an opening along the fence, maintained a short lead over rivals on both sides through the final furlong and held gamely to the wire. SANTOS TO WILSON bumped outer rival in the beginning, had to steady behind JAMMING EDDY early, chased two wide into the turn, angled out and came five wide into the lane, rallied down the middle part of the track but could not get by the winner. JAMMING EDDY stalked the pace from inside into the turn, saved ground around the bend, gained a clear run up the fence when LAMBEAU moved off the rail into the lane, challenged from inside, had the rider lose the whip at the eighth pole, continued gamely under hand urging but lacked the needed late punch in deep stretch. ESTABLISHED raced up close outside rivals, bid three deep on the turn, fought four deep into the final furlong, finished gamely but got outkicked in the end. IMPOSSIBLE TASK took a bump from inside at the start, chased outside a rival then three wide into the turn, eased out around the bend and traveled six wide turning for home but failed to rally when needed. DISKO TRIBUTE forwardly placed between rivals, challenged between rivals on the turn, fought to the eighth pole and weakened.

ANGELCENTS chased along the rail into the turn, spun two wide into the lane, cut back inside to challenge outer trio and was no match for the winner late. DANCING SOUL dueled outside SHE'S RESILIENT up the backstretch and around the turn, got floated out a bit to the three path entering the lane, fought between rivals to the eighth pole, could not kick on in the furlong grounds but managed to save the show. A NEW PEACE traveled two wide at the back into the turn, entered the lane four wide, offered a mild response to urging and missed the show. ON PURPOSE tracked in the two path, spun three wide into the lane and lacked further response. SHE'S RESILIENT went up to duel with DANCING SOUL, fought into and around the bend, drifted out a bit into the lane, stayed on to the eighth pole, then weakened. RACE.FOOTNOTES: CALIFORNIA TIGER dueled between rivals then outside CAROL'S COMIC on the turn, cleared that rival at the quarter pole and drew away in the furlong grounds under urging. EL REY DORADO was off a bit slow to begin, chased two wide into and around the turn, finished willingly through the lane but could not threaten the winner. JOHN DUNBAR away quickly from outside, pressed three deep to the turn, chased inner rivals then after the lone leader three wide around the bend, could not make any headway on the winner late but kept on to secure the show. CAROL'S COMIC dueled for command from inside, getting out while the rider did his best to keep her from drifting approaching the quarter pole, continued along the rail into the lane, tried to drifted again in upper stretch and had to be corrected, then weakened in the late stages. SMILING RULER chased greenly up the backstretch while coaxed along, entered the turn along the rail, dropped back around the bend, raced three wide turning for home and had little left for the stretch run.

KING APOLLO traveled along the inside near the back into the turn, steered out around the bend and spun four wide into the lane, angled out widest to unleash a rally and was gaining to the wire. PRINCE LANCELOT (GB) broke a bit slow, moved into range under coaxing from inside, continued to draw closer on the turn, tipped two wide into the lane, challenged the leader past the eighth pole, got floated out at the sixteenth marker and lacked the needed late punch. SAWASDEE set the pace under pressure from outer rival, cleared around the bend, asked right handed at the eighth pole, tested by PRINCE LANCELOT (GB) shortly after, drifted out entering the final sixteenth and yielded late. INCH settled outside rivals then had to steady at the half-mile pole, rounded the bend two then three wide, summoned a mild rally and improved position. MISTER ICEMAN raced up close between rivals then chased two wide into the turn, got shuffled behind a rival at the five-sixteenths pole, angled to the inside, tipped out in upper stretch, chased within striking distance with a furlong remaining, got floated out at the sixteenth pole and flattened. VORPAL was off a bit slow in the beginning, trailed on the inside to the stretch and could not threaten. SILARDI chased five then three deep early, remained three deep into the turn, bumped with inner rival at the quarter pole, spun four wide into the lane and weakened. PAT'S PADDOCK PICK pressed the leader up the backstretch, lost touch with that rival early on the turn, chased between foes and bumped with SILARDI at the quarter pole, then weakened down the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DEVIL MOON took control early and set the pace outside K P KWEST, cleared that rival approaching the quarter pole, moved over to the inside leaving the bend, continued clear into deep stretch, grew a bit weary late but was able to hold on. BUCK OWENS coaxed along near the back, left the backstretch three wide then dove down to the rail on the turn, tipped out into the stretch, rallied steadily through the lane and just missed. RACE.FOOTNOTES: LAKOTA SPIRIT tracked the pace from inside through both turns, launched a bid along the fence in upper stretch, took over in the furlong grounds and drew clear late. BOLT'S BROAD brushed at the start, traveled between rivals off the pace early, drew closer two to three wide on the far turn, tipped out and challenged four deep in upper stretch, was outkicked by LAKOTA SPIRIT in deep stretch and held the place. LUMINIFEROUS stalked from the two path, asked right handed at the quarter pole, turned for home four wide, finished willingly but could not get by BOLT'S BROAD for second. KLEEN KARMA bumped with outer rival at the start, sat off the pace along the rail, tipped out in upper stretch, altered inward midstretch and finished willingly for a minor placing. IDESSIA bumped with inner rival at the start, trailed early on the inside, moved out and went four deep into the far turn, steered out further in the drive and lacked the needed response. ANKYRAH pulled early between rivals, chased three deep into and around the far turn and faded down the lane. MYFAVORITEDAUGHTER set the pace early in the two path, took pressure on the backstretch then cleared at the half-mile pole, pressured by TIERGARTEN again entering the lane, lost command in upper stretch, bothered by outer rival coming in and steadied midstretch and gave way.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MR FISK chased along the three path early, bid three deep at the seven-sixteenths pole, lost touch with the top pair past the five-sixteenths pole, challenged again three deep into the lane, kicked clear midstretch and held safely over SKINNER late. SKINNER came away cleanly then dropped back early, trailed in the three path around the clubhouse turn, advanced four deep in the middle stages, lost ground on the far turn while in the four path, kept on willingly in the drive to gain the place but could not reach the winner. NEWGRANGE stalked in the two path, bid between leaving the backstretch, dueled outside ARROWTHEGREAT on the far turn, carried a short lead into the stretch, put away inner rival then fought with MR FISK to the eighth pole, lost command shortly after and weakened. ARROWTHEGREAT took control early and set the pace on the inside, met bids from outer rivals at the seven-sixteenths pole, dueled inside NEWGRANGE through the far turn, lost command leaving the bend and gave way in the stretch run. KISS TODAY GOODBYE tracked two wide early, went between rivals in the middle stages, chased two wide then spun four wide into the lane and came up empty in the lane. CELESTIAL MOON broke a step slow, moved inside to give chase but began to climb, continued with the awkward gait around the clubhouse turn, up the backstretch and into the far turn, angled out and came five wide into the lane and failed to menace. VISITANT stalked along the inside, started to weaken on the far turn and tired in the stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ONE OF THESE DAYS (IRE) reserved three deep early then started to pull first time in the stretch, tucked inside towards the rear on the clubhouse turn, remained inside on the far turn, steered out in the lane, closed between rivals in deep stretch and got up at the wire. KHANTARO D'ORO settled along the rail, saved ground to the stretch, angled out to make a run, rallied and got brushed at the sixteenth pole, finished gamely five deep late, drifted in near the wire and missed. CAPTAIN CHOOCHIES vied four deep leaving the chute then stalked outside a pair of rivals, moved into the two path on the first turn, traveled between rivals in the middle stages, came under a ride on the far turn, asked three wide into the stretch, rallied and brushed with outer rival into the final sixteenth and missed between foes in a blanket finish. SURF AFFAIR showed early speed inside a outer trio leaving the chute, took a stalking position along the rail first time in the stretch, went two wide into the lane, bid between foes in upper stretch, took a narrow lead late but was outkicked in the closing moments. PLAYER B vied three deep leaving the chute then raced two wide while closest in pursuit, moved up to challenge from outside past the three-eighths pole and dueled around the far turn, carried a short lead into the stretch, moved clear at the eighth pole, soon challenged from both sides in the final sixteenth, yielded late and steadied at the wire. ASHCROFT pulled early and became rank between rivals, settled outside a rival or in the two path, spun three wide into the lane, angled out widest and kept on while needing more to threaten. STARFORCE broke a bit slow from inside, trailed along the rail to the stretch and offered a mild response to pass tired rivals. SEA OF CORTEZ (IRE) bumped with outer rival not too long after the start, lost his path and took hold briefly in the chute, went four deep into the stretch for the first time then became rank early, rounded the clubhouse turn three then two wide racing near the back, ridden along on the far turn and put to left handed urging but failed to menace in the lane. GHOST COAST raced five deep leaving the chute then chased four to three deep on the first turn, rounded the far turn three then four wide and also weakened. CARIBBEAN KING took a bump from inside shortly after the start, vied between leaving the chute then cleared and moved inside, set the pace to the far turn, dueled for command with outer rival around the bend, lost the lead entering the stretch and retreated.
